00:15:04.080 --> 00:15:05.840
Now here's something important.

00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:10.320
Notice what we're not including in this simulator, fraud scores.

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:11.359
This is intentional.

00:15:11.919 --> 00:15:16.719
In a real system, raw transactions arrive without fraud indicators.

00:15:16.719 --> 00:15:19.520
The machine learning model scores them separately.

00:15:20.159 --> 00:15:24.400
This separation of concerns is critical for production systems.

00:15:25.119 --> 00:15:27.359
If we generated fraud scores here,

00:15:27.359 --> 00:15:31.200
we'd be mixing data ingestion with fraud detection,

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:34.400
